FBIS3-30110 "dreas038_a_94016" FBIS-EAS-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 February 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Tokyo To Hold CIS Seminar on Export Controls OW2502115394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1057 GMT 25 Feb 94 OW2502115394 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 25 KYODO -- Japan will brief 12 former Soviet republics on its measures on arms control, disarmament and nonproliferation when it holds a seminar on export control March 7- 11, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [25 February]. The seminar will be the first including all 12 former Soviet republics to discuss controls on the export of technology with military applications and will be sponsored by the Foreign Ministry in cooperation with the Ministries of Finance, and International Trade and Industry. The seminar is designed to assist the former republics in establishing an effective export control system in order to strengthen the nonproliferation of arms, the ministry said.
